#   BE-005: unify verb output via the shared ROWS/HUNK state banner

`be`'s verb reports must all speak ONE output model: stream color to a
tty, compose ONE `H` hunk per (sub)module for `--tlv`, each headed by a
pale-yellow *state banner* — built through ROWS, never per-site
`fprintf` or a pasted `THEME_BANNER`. Today only the per-file tables
comply; the summaries / confirmations (`be get`, post/put, `status!`)
still print raw. This is the umbrella; per-verb wiring lands as the
child tickets [GET-026], [STATUS-001], [POST-018].

##  Input

### Context
 -  ROWS (`dog/ROWS.c`) is the shared builder: `status` opens it with
    `uri="status:"` + `ROWS_BATCH` → one banner hunk (`SNIFF.exe.c:457`).
 -  The get checkout opens ROWS with `empty_uri` + `ROWS_MODE_KEYED`;
    `rows_stream_one` (`ROWS.c:172`) zeroes ts/verb/uri → flat, NO banner.
 -  The banner IS the hunk header, single-sourced via `HUNKu8sFeedBanner`
    keyed on the hunk's `uri/verb/ts` and the global `HUNKMode`.
 -  Verb-bang already wired (`DOG_BANG_VERB`/`cli.bang`); `be x!` ≡
    `be x --force` — the [STATUS-001] extended toggle.

### Goals
 -  ONE model for every verb report: ROWS table, state-banner header,
    `HUNKMode`-keyed (color stream on tty / one `H` hunk on `--tlv`).
 -  Streaming ROWS emits the module banner ONCE before the first row (and
    on an empty result) — so KEYED (get/clone) matches BATCH (status).
 -  Per-verb wiring split into [GET-026], [STATUS-001], [POST-018]; each
    links back here and reuses the same ROWS banner path.

### Constraints
 -  No copy-pasted banner code at call sites — only the ROWS module-hunk
    header. `dog/ROWS` + `sniff/` only; no `abc/` ([abc-changes-need-review]).
 -  Preserve live streaming for big clones (KEYED); do NOT force BATCH.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Core change in `dog/ROWS.c`: a streaming table with a non-empty
    `uri/verb/ts` emits its banner once (and on empty), vs zeroing it —
    the single enabler every child depends on.
 -  Children supply only their banner uri + rows; the banner, mode-keying
    and `--tlv` relay stay in ROWS/HUNK.

